<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>local.pxx.mini-vllm-tunnel</string>

    <!--
      Mac Mini variant: TWO local-forwards over ONE ssh connection to the gpu-node-1.

        127.0.0.1:8001 -> gpu-node-1 loopback:8001 -> (vllm-host-1 reverse tunnel) -> Qwen3-Coder
        127.0.0.1:8003 -> gpu-node-1 loopback:8003 -> qwen2.5-coder-14b   (fallback)

      Paired with:
        PXX_VLLM_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8001,http://127.0.0.1:8003
        PXX_VLLM_MODEL=openai/Qwen3-Coder,openai/qwen2.5-coder-14b-coder-lora

      WHY LOOPBACK, NOT THE LAN ADDRESS: macOS Local Network privacy (TCC)
      blocks pxx's Python from reaching LAN addresses when launched from
      launchd -- the exact context the WhatsApp bridge runs in. It presents as
      an intermittent "No Ollama or vLLM endpoint reachable"/"No route to
      host" that never reproduces from a terminal, because an interactive
      session already holds the grant. /usr/bin/ssh is NOT subject to the gate,
      so the tunnel does the LAN hop and pxx only ever touches localhost, which
      is exempt. This tunnel is a correctness requirement, not a convenience.

      ExitOnForwardFailure guards the LOCAL bind only. If vllm-host-1's reverse
      tunnel is down, :8001 still binds and pxx's probe fails at request time,
      falling through to :8003 -- which is the intended degradation.

      Requires an `ssh gpu-node-1` alias in ~/.ssh/config. Replace /Users/you
      with your $HOME.
    -->

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/usr/bin/ssh</string>
        <string>-N</string>
        <string>-F</string>
        <string>/Users/you/.ssh/config</string>
        <string>-o</string>
        <string>ServerAliveInterval=30</string>
        <string>-o</string>
        <string>ServerAliveCountMax=3</string>
        <string>-o</string>
        <string>ExitOnForwardFailure=yes</string>
        <string>-o</string>
        <string>StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new</string>
        <string>-L</string>
        <string>127.0.0.1:8001:127.0.0.1:8001</string>
        <string>-L</string>
        <string>127.0.0.1:8003:127.0.0.1:8003</string>
        <string>gpu-node-1</string>
    </array>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>
    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>15</integer>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>HOME</key>
        <string>/Users/you</string>
    </dict>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Users/you/Library/Logs/pxx-gpu-node-1-tunnel.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Users/you/Library/Logs/pxx-gpu-node-1-tunnel.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
